npc/gatekeeper: Wait. Before you reach that door — look at it. It is locked.
npc/gatekeeper: Every place like this is easy to walk into. Walking out is the part they never advertise.
npc/gatekeeper: Most people think the way out is one more win. One big payout to cover everything they lost. That key never drops.
npc/gatekeeper: I searched for it for two years. I borrowed money. I chased losses. I lied to people who loved me. The door stayed shut.
npc/gatekeeper: You know what finally opened it? Not luck. Not money. Admitting I needed help — and letting someone hand me the key.
npc/gatekeeper: So I am handing it to you. Take it. This is what getting out actually looks like.
npc/gatekeeper: One more thing, because you will need it out there.
npc/gatekeeper: When this place sinks its hooks into you — and it will — the worst thing you can do is freeze and let it pull you deeper.
npc/gatekeeper: The people who get out are the ones who move the instant they see the trap for what it is. They break away before it closes.
npc/gatekeeper: So take this — a burst of speed. Learn to dash clear the moment something feels wrong. Don't wait around. Don't "see how it goes."
npc/gatekeeper: Now go. The door will open for you.
